2) Critical severity
Suggested fix: Use parameterized queries or prepared statements to prevent SQL injection. For example, if using a MySQL database, you can use the following code:
```javascript
app.post('/api/admin/delete-user', (req, res) => {
  const userId = req.body.id;
  db.query('DELETE FROM users WHERE id = ?', [userId]);
  res.json({ success: true });
});
```
If using a different database, refer to the appropriate documentation for parameterized queries.

